    <!-- Orientation Checklist -->
    <template id="orientation_checklist">
        <t t-call="web.html_container">
            <t t-foreach="docs" t-as="doc">
                <t t-call="ibas_hris.ibas_external_layout_boxed2">
                    <div class="page">
                     <link href="/ibas_hris/static/css/ibas.css"
                                rel="stylesheet" type="text/css"/>
                        <p style="text-align: center;"><strong>ORIENTATION CHECKLIST</strong></p>
                        <p><strong>Documentation:  Necessary papers to be signed and requirements to be submitted</strong></p>
                    
                        <ol class="m-left-62 line-height-2">
                            <li>Hiring Contract/Job Description/Position Orientation/Major Duties and Responsibilities</li>
                            <li>Confidentiality Agreement</li>
                            <li>Social Security System (SSS) / Tax Identification Number (TIN)</li>
                            <li>Philippine Health Insurance Corporation – Philhealth</li>
                            <li>Home Development Mutual Fund – HDMF or Pag-ibig Fund    </li>
                            <li>Police Clearance and/or NBI Clearance/Barangay Certificate</li>
                            <li>Medical Tests/Drug test/X-Ray/Others – expenses will be shouldered by the newly hired 
                            employee while succeeding required annual tests during the employment will be shouldered by the company.</li>
                        </ol>
                        <br/>
                        <p><strong>Getting started:  Orientation on the following company details</strong></p>
                     
                        <ol class="m-left-62 line-height-2">
                            <li>Company and Departmental Organizational Chart </li>
                            <li>Company Policy and Employee Manual
                                <ul>
                                    <li>Work shift hours and Overtime; Cut-off and Pay days; Dress Code and Uniform; 
                                    Filing of Leave of Absence, Undertime and Tardiness; Lunch and Snack Breaks; </li>
                                </ul>
                            </li>
                            <li>Company Safety Rules and Health Hazard – let the new employee provide a list of names, 
                            addresses and contact numbers of persons to contact for emergency cases; 
                            Orientation will be based on Safety Procedure from ISO </li>
                            <li>Introduction to assigned department and co-employees and/or Work Site Familiarization/Tour of the work areas and other facilities of the company (files/records; lunch and restroom areas; 
                            office supplies and other special equipment; Policies on telephone, mobile and internet usage)</li>
                        </ol>
                     
                        <p><strong>Departmental Orientation: Introduce to Department Head and co-employees/staff</strong></p>
                        <ol class="m-left-62 line-height-2">
                        <li>Departmental Policies and House Rules – Proper completion and deadlines; Assignment of initial work items; 
                        Performance expectations; General operating procedure</li>   
                        <li>Performance Standards and Training Procedures: (Ask new hire if he has attended training and/or seminars which may be related to his present job assignment; 
                        Set a performance rating for the new hire as guidelines for his evaluation.) </li>   
                        </ol>
                        <p> This is to acknowledge that all the above details have been discussed and oriented to me clearly.   
                        Any concerns which may arise from the above orientation should be discussed and be given priority actions. </p>  
                        <br/>
                        <p>Conforme:</p>
                        <br/>
                        <br/>
                        <p class='uppercase'><span t-field="doc.first_name"/> <span t-field="doc.last_name"/></p>
                        <p class="overline">Printed Name and Signature</p>
                        <br/>
                        <p>Date: <span class="underline" t-esc="context_timestamp(datetime.datetime.now()).strftime('%B-%d-%Y')"/> </p>
                    </div>
                </t>
            </t>
        </t>
    </template>

